  "title": "Sales and Marketing Executive #78383",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Electronics Manufacturing</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Sales and Marketing Executive</strong></li><li>Working Location: Tampines</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Mon – Fri, 8.30am – 5.30pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $5,000 + Transport Allowance + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage a broad range of semiconductor and electronic component products for OEMs, EMS providers, and independent distributors in regional and international markets.</li><li>Build and maintain strong relationships with regional agents and global trading partners to ensure smooth supply and alignment with business goals.</li><li>Work with engineering, procurement, and R&D to understand technical needs and provide suitable component solutions.</li><li>Find and pursue new sales opportunities to grow market share in both high‑volume and niche component segments.</li><li>Support existing clients to drive satisfaction, retention, and repeat orders.</li><li>Advise on product specifications, compatibility, and applications to support informed purchasing.</li><li>Respond promptly to pricing, availability, order status, and logistics enquiries.</li><li>Follow up after sales to troubleshoot issues and maintain ongoing relationships.</li><li>Track sales results and KPIs; prepare regular reports to guide strategy and improve forecasts.</li><li>Handle inbound enquiries and follow up on leads quickly and professionally to convert them.</li><li>Work with supply chain, logistics, and finance to complete orders smoothly and keep customers satisfied.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Electronics/Electrical or related field.</li><li>Strong knowledge of semiconductor and electronic components, including uses and market trends.</li><li>Experience working with agents, distributors, and trading partners in the electronics supply chain.</li><li>Good understanding of sales channels and distribution models in the semiconductor sector.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#78383 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
